## Working with repos

- Each subdirectory is an independent git clone with its own `.git`. Always `cd` into the repo directory before running git commands.
- Branches, commits, and pushes happen per-repo, not at the workspace root.
- Each repo may have its own `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, or `openspec/AGENTS.md` with repo-specific instructions. Read those before making changes.

## Conventions

- Infrastructure code uses OpenTofu/Terraform with Terramate orchestration.
- In `parloa-infra-pre-stamp/`: do not edit `*.tm.hcl` files directly. Modify the templates, then run `uv run scripts/generate-terramate-stacks.py` followed by `terramate generate` and `terramate fmt`.
- Stamps are defined as YAML manifests in `stamps-catalog/stamps/`.
- Release channels are managed in `stamps-release-channels/`.

## Git workflow

- Create feature branches, never push directly to `main`.
- Follow existing commit message conventions in each repo.
- Run linters and formatters before committing.

